social_posts.post_text: When the @local_706 hair & makeup guild awards says you can make a collage with your submission this year 💃 // Here is a glimpse of what my @euphoria makeup team and I created together for Season 2. Seeing so much of it all together gives me the happy sappy emo chills! Becoming a momma and a creative director for a makeup line this past year has me slacking on my IG makeup posts but I wanted to share this lil visual feast w/ y’all ❤️ // If you’re a fellow @local_706 member please consider @tlangmakeup @alexandraafrench and I for best contemporary makeup on a TV show! #euphoriamakeup #euphoriaseason2 #euphoria

My alien glam on @dylanmulvaney for a truly profound photo shoot about holding back, transformation and rebirth, led by mastermind & photographer @illumitati . This is part of a larger series which is showcased on Tati and Dylan’s IGs ❤️

This photo is from the “FINAL FORM” part of the series which is all about rebirth and allowing full expression of oneself. I don’t think you need to know all of who you are to express yourself through makeup, hair, fashion, etc. Like, I don’t think it has to make sense or be justified in any way to yourself or to others because so much of it as about self discovery and trying on different versions of ourselves. We don’t have to commit to any one singular version of ourselves, ever, at any point in our lives. Like, how could we possibly know all of who we are, and even if we did why would we want to stop there? So basically, what gives us the right to hold ourselves back!?

Shout out to the awesome @hubblestudio for hosting this shoot! Thank you 🙏

Makeup: @donni.davy using @halfmagicbeauty 🪄✨

This look on @dylanmulvaney was inspired by silent movie star makeup. This is a closeup of an image that’s part of a larger photo series about personal metamorphosis — an incredible collaboration led by @illumitati. Check out Dylan and Tati’s post to see the complete series. Swipe to see some images that inspired me. 

This photo is from the “BOUND” part of the series which is all about the versions of you that exist just under the surface — the ones that are more YOU than ever before. Hope and fear exist together here, and bravery is necessary to move forward. I respect Dylan so much for wanting to do this shoot that would capture the darker emotional space that comes before personal metamorphosis ⛓🖤🦋

Shout out to the awesome Hubble Studio for hosting this shoot! Thank you 🙏

Angus. His kind, sweet demeanor on the show was just how he was in real life. He was bashfully charming and brought the Euphoria makeup trailer joy and laughter — loads of it. He brought his amazing Mom into the makeup trailer once, and I was so excited to meet this woman — to connect a mother to this incredible guy. We talked about how awesome and lovable her son is. I’m thinking of her now and sending her all the love I have. Angus will be thought of, spoken about and remembered all the damn time by his Euphoria family. We were so lucky to have known him.

Kevin Turen… I will never forget when he (and Ravi from A24) called me during the summer of 2019 after Euphoria Season 1 aired and asked me if I wanted to start my own makeup line. It wasn’t like an abstract idea. It was like a fully committed, “We believe in you and your work. If you want to do this we got you, period.” 

I only knew Kevin on set, but his presence was really, really bright and I’ll always remember his electric enthusiasm and how fast and excitedly he talked about the people and projects he believed in. When I shared with him that I was pregnant during the filming of Season 2, he smiled really big and said, “my kids have been the most amazing adventure of my life!!”

I’m still processing Angus’s passing and it’s hard to believe this news about Kevin. I’m sending love to all his loved ones, especially to his kids and Evelina, and also to the entire Euphoria family, and everyone who shares in this sadness.
